\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. R. tetraspis} Pallas,{\i  Reise}{\b  1}: 486 (1771). Stems 18-50 cm, glabrous. Basal leaves (7-)12-18(-22) × (1-)2-3·5 cm, lanceolate to narrowly ovate, glabrous; cauline leaves smaller, the upper cuneate to cordate, sessile, with sub-lanate apices. Inflorescence paniculate. Pedicels 5-10 mm, elongating in fruit. Calyx 5-7 mm, villous. Corolla 12-14 mm, subconical, lobed to ½ ; lobes linear-oblong, purple; tube yellowish; invaginations small, at middle of corolla. Stamens included; anthers ½ as long as corolla-lobes. Nutlets 16 mm.{\i  Stony slopes. S. part of U.S.S.R}. Rs (C, W, K, E).
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. R. umbellata} (Waldst. & Kit.) Bunge,{\i  Beitr. Kenntn. Fl. Russl.} 239 (1852). Stems 25-70 cm, hirsute. Basal leaves (7-)12-25 × 0·7-2 cm, linear-lanceolate to oblong-elliptical, sparsely sericeous; cauline leaves smaller, lanceolate, the upper narrowly ovate to oblanceolate. Inflorescence subumbellate. Pedicels 3-5 mm, elongating in fruit. Calyx 11-15 mm, sericeous. Corolla 11-15 mm, subconical, lobed to 1/3; lobes broadly oblong, yellow; invaginations above middle of corolla. Stamens equalling corolla. Nutlets 14 mm.{\i  Dry,open habitats. • From E. Jugoslavia to S.W. Ukraine.} Bu Ju Rm Rs (W).
\par

