\pard\f0\fs28 Annual or perennial herbs or small shrubs. Leaves opposite or rarely in whorls of 3. Flowers in bracteate spikes, usually arranged in panicles or corymbs. Calyx tubular, 5-ribbed and unequally 5-dentate. Corolla hypocrateriform, weakly 2-lipped, with obtuse or emarginate lobes. Stamens inserted at about the middle of the corolla-tube, included. Stigma unequally 2-lobed. Fruit separating at maturity into 4 nutlets.
\par

